<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 07 at 5:27AM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 545 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN SEARCY...SOUTHEASTERN NEWTON...NORTHWESTERN VAN
BUREN AND NORTHEASTERN POPE COUNTIES...
At 525 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Tilly, or 18
miles southwest of Marshall, moving east at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Witts Spring...                   Imo...
Ben Hur...                        Chimes...
Tilly...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.50 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
